To study the growth and evolution of perturbations outside of the linear regime, we simulate the fully non-linear PDEs using the method described in Section \ref{sec:remodel}, using the monochromatic perturbation with fastest linear growth rate as an initial condition. If the fastest growing linear perturbation has wavenumber $k_{\rm max}$ we solve the evolution equations in a periodic domain of size $2\pi/k_{\rm max}$. We find that, starting with very small perturbations, the density profile evolves toward a soliton (Fig. \ref{fig:nonlinearevoln}). The soliton solution is described mathematically in the main-text and in Section \ref{sec:anti-jams}.
